M a l e: Protarsomeres 1 to 3 hardly widened. Aedeagus (
Figs 196-198
) 0.35-0.40 mm long, symmetrical, with basal bulb weakly sclerotized, except for its oblique, strongly sclerotized apical side. Articular processes small, not prominent. Apical process of median lobe trifid. Ventral branch of apical process narrow, weakly inflexed, tapering dorsal view, even in lateral view, lacking tubercles. Dorsal branches of apical process tapering. Parameres in lateral view sinuate, widest in middle part and strongly narrowed apically, in dorsal view almost straight in basal halves, curved and gradually narrowed in apical halves. Internal sac with central membranous vesicle covered by scale-like structures, partly overlapping long and fairly sclerotized admesal spines.
